        {
            "id": 2131094,
            "is_internal": false,
            "editable": false,
            "type": "Activities::Comment",
            "message": "I think you have misunderstood my report @philip, the security impact here is when a disabled user change a password via password reset link `there will be no notification in user's end.`\n\nWhen changing password via `https://hackerone.com/settings/pass/edit` then the user will be notified via email. Which is a good practice\n\nWhen changing password for enabled users/active user via __Password Reset Links__ `https://hackerone.com/users/password/edit` then the user will be notified via email. Which is a good practice.\n\nBut when changing password for disabled users/inactive user via __Password Reset Links__ `https://hackerone.com/users/password/edit` the user will not be notified via email. Which is a bad practice. The user should be notified also since you can re-enable an account after it has been disabled.\n\nIf an attacker has a valid password reset link then the inactive victim will not be notified that his/her password was changed. Are you really okay with that @philip?",
            "automated_response": false,
