        {
            "id": 2163993,
            "is_internal": false,
            "editable": false,
            "type": "Activities::AgreedOnGoingPublic",
            "message": "Hi @clarckowen_ - wanted to follow up on your last comments. This seems to be a regression on our end, but we decided not to implement a fix for the time being and are accepting the risk here. This is a missing best practice, not an immediate security vulnerability. We might get around implementing this again at one point. Happy to publicly disclose this!\n\n> It only needs a valid reset link for example left by the victim's computer in an office or computer shops then the victim will never notice that his/her password was changed.\n\nThis is not a feasible attack scenario. [Immutable Law of Security #3](https://technet.microsoft.com/library/cc722487.aspx#EIAA): If a bad guy has unrestricted physical access to your computer, it's not your computer anymore.\n\nThanks for your contribution and bringing this to our attention, but, again, we're not publishing a fix for this at this moment. Happy hacking!\n\nJobert",
            "automated_response": false,
